Total occlusion of iliac arteries: results of balloon angioplasty. Fifty-six occluded iliac arteries (mean length 6.1 cm range 1-17 cm) in 50 patients were treated by percutaneous transluminal angioplasty (PTA) or laser-assisted PTA (bilateral lesions in 6 patients). Twenty-seven patients (54%) were at high risk for surgery. Patients were followed for a maximum period of 72 months (mean 23.12 months